        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 4:09PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 408 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles northwest of Buckhannon, moving north at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Clarksburg, Grafton, Philippi, Audra State Park, Bridgeport,
Stonewood, Nutter Fort, Salem, Anmoore, Jackson Mill, West Milford,
Lost Creek, Jane Lew, Flemington, Wolf Summit, Meadland, Tygart Lake
State Park, Despard, Moatsville, and Volga.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 79 between mile markers 102 and 125.
Route 50 in West Virginia between mile markers 66 and 82.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
